<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="299" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="20.[1865,3504,1536,2849]" pageId="20" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1867,2337,2604,2643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="299">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[2348,2422,2604,2643]" country="Cameroon" name="North" pageId="20" pageNumber="299">Not</collectingRegion>
assessed on 
<emphasis box="[2657,2987,2604,2643]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="299">The IUCNRed List.</emphasis>
Virtually nothing is known about the Kahuzi Horseshoe 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2417,2482,2655,2694]" pageId="20" pageNumber="299">Bat</emphasis>
because it was newly recognized in 2007 from a single specimen collected in 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:885887A2FFDB8A3DF882FCA9F510D242:052E606FFFDB8A3DF6CDF537F49DD3DE" box="[2305,2840,2710,2749]" name="Kahuzi-Biega National Park" pageId="20" pageNumber="299" stateProvince="North">Kahuzi-Biéga National Park</location>
. Additional research is needed to assess its ecology and conservation status.
</paragraph>
